        <h4>
            Biography of Pastor Stan Gale</h4>
    </p>
    <p>
        <img src="~/images/SDG pic1-1.jpg" width="150" height="144" runat="server" /></p>
    <p>
        Stanley D. Gale has served as pastor of RPC since 1988.&nbsp; He and his wife, Linda,
        married in 1975.&nbsp; They have four children and four grandchildren.&nbsp; He holds
        Bachelor of Arts and Master of Education degrees from the University of Delaware,
        a Master of Divinity degree from Westminster Theological Seminary in Philadelphia,
        and a Doctor of Ministry degree from Covenant Theological Seminary in St. Louis.&nbsp;
        In 2003 he launched a prayer-based outreach ministry called Community House of Prayer
        <a href="http://www.chopministry.net">(www.CHOPministry.net)</a>.&nbsp; He is the author of <em>Community Houses of Prayer Ministry
            Manual:&nbsp; Reaching People for Christ through Strategic Prayer</em>, <em>Warfare
                Witness: Contending With Spiritual Opposition in Everyday Evangelism</em>,
        <em>GOD&rsquo;s good news: a summary of the Bible&rsquo;s message of life</em>,
        and <em>The Prayer of Jehoshaphat: Seeing Beyond Life&rsquo;s Storms</em>, as well
        as a variety of articles and reviews.</p>
